jQuery plugin for basic tab functionality

Call on the parent(s) containing both tabs and tab-containers.

Adds the class "current" to both tab and container, style as you like.


Example:

<section id="example">
	<ul class="tabs">
		<li><a href="page1.html">Tab 1</a></li>
		<li><a href="page2.html">Tab 2</a></li>
	</ul>
	<div class="tab-containers">
		<article>Container 1</article>
		<article>Container 2</article>
	</div>
</section>

<script>
$(function() {
	
	// initiate tabs
	$('#example').tabify();

});
</script>

<style>
.tab-containers article {
	display: none;
}
.tab-containers .current {
	display: block;
}
</style>